<p />
<h2><a name="Abstract"> Abstract </a></h2>
<p />
Radio <a href="/twiki/bin/view/Main/UserLand">UserLand</a> is <span style='background : #FFFFCE;'><font color="#0000FF">Frontier</font></span><a href="/twiki/bin/edit/Main/Frontier?topicparent=Main.RadioUserLand">?</a>'s little brother, produced by <a href="/twiki/bin/view/Main/DaveWiner">DaveWiner</a>'s <a href="/twiki/bin/view/Main/UserLand">UserLand</a>.  It is a full <span style='background : #FFFFCE;'><font color="#0000FF">WebAppServer</font></span><a href="/twiki/bin/edit/Main/WebAppServer?topicparent=Main.RadioUserLand">?</a> on the desktop, based on <span style='background : #FFFFCE;'><font color="#0000FF">Frontier</font></span><a href="/twiki/bin/edit/Main/Frontier?topicparent=Main.RadioUserLand">?</a>.  Out of the box, it provides <span style='background : #FFFFCE;'><font color="#0000FF">NewsAggregation</font></span><a href="/twiki/bin/edit/Main/NewsAggregation?topicparent=Main.RadioUserLand">?</a> and reciprocal <a href="/twiki/bin/view/Main/WebLog">WebLog</a> functionality, as well as an exposed architecture suitable for drop-in apps and plugins.
<p />
<a href="http://radio.userland.com/" target="_top">http://radio.userland.com/</a>
<p />
<h2><a name="Resources"> Resources </a></h2>
<p />
<ul>
<li> Radio-Dev mailing list: <a href="http://groups.yahoo.com/group/radio-dev/" target="_top">http://groups.yahoo.com/group/radio-dev/</a>
</li>
</ul>
